{{refimprove|date=January 2013}} {{Infobox settlement | name = Chabahil | other_name = Chabel{{citation needed|date=July 2018}} | image_skyline = Chabahil.stupa.jpg | image_alt = | image_caption = Chabahil Chowk |subdivision_type = Country |subdivision_name = [[Nepal]]<!-- the name of the country, not the flag --> |subdivision_type2 = [[Districts of Nepal|District]] |subdivision_type1 = [[Provinces of Nepal|Province]] |subdivision_name2 = Kathmandu |subdivision_name1 = [[Province No. 3]] |population_blank1_title = Ethnicities |population_blank1 = [[Newar]], [[Bahun]], [[Chhetri]], [[Tamang]], [[Magars|Magar]] |postal_code_type = Postal Code |postal_code = 44602 |area_code = 01 |website = |footnotes = |timezone = [[Nepal Standard Time|NST]] |utc_offset = +5:45 | settlement_type = City | pushpin_map = Nepal | pushpin_label_position = bottom | pushpin_mapsize = 300 | pushpin_map_caption = Location in Nepal | coordinates = {{coord|27|43|02|N|85|20|47|E|region:NP|display=title}} | population_total = 85195 | population_as_of = 2011 }}
[[Image:Chabahil Chowk.jpg|thumb|The main ''Chowk'' (square) of Chabahil]] '''Chabahil''' ({{lang-ne|चाबहिल}}) (also [[Kathmandu Metropolitan City]] Ward 07<ref>{{cite web |title=Ward 07 |url=http://www.kathmandu.gov.np/sites/kathmandu.gov.np/files/ward%207.pdf |publisher=Kathmandu Metropolitan City |accessdate=1 July 2018}}</ref>)is an ancient neighbourhood at the northeastern side of the [[Kathmandu]] in [[Nepal]]. It is famous for its [[Licchavi (kingdom)|Licchavi]] [[stupa]], called the Dhando Chaitya considered by many historians to be the oldest [[Buddhist Stupa]] in the valley. Currently, Chabahil has become a thriving residential and commercial area of [[Kathmandu]]. Apart from the large temples, there are many more small temples around them. Two of the most important temples in Kathmandu, [[Pashupatinath Temple|Pashupatinath]] and [[Guhyeswari]] are situated very close to Chabahil. These two temples, dedicated to Lord [[Shiva]] and his consort [[Sati (goddess)|Sati]] are considered to be more than a thousand years old.{{citation needed|date=July 2018}}
==Charumati Vihara== The stupa has attracted [[Buddhist]] monks and other pilgrims over the centuries. According to the inscriptions found within it, it was built by the Indian princess [[Charumati]], daughter of Indian Emperor Ashoka, who was married to a Nepalese prince in [[Kathmandu]].<ref>''Dhanavajra Vajracharya''', Licchavikalin Abhilekha, Kathmandu : Nepal Asiali Adyayan Sansthan, 2030 B.S. p-392</ref> Near the Charumati Vihara, there is a beautiful stone statue of Buddha that is a meter high.{{citation needed|date=July 2018}}
==Chandra Binayak Temple== Another landmark located in the town is the temple of Chandra Binayak [[Ganesh]], the Hindu god with the head of an elephant and the body of a man. which is the youngest son of shiva Hindu god. The temple, located on the main market street of Chabahil, is one of the four temples of Binayak in the Kathmandu Valley. Devotees flock to this century-old temple especially on Tuesdays (and other days when Lord Ganesh is worshiped).{{citation needed|date=July 2018}}
