'''Endurance Ridge''' ({{coord|62|30|S|40|0|W|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is an Antarctic [[Mid-ocean ridge|undersea ridge]], south-east of [[Coronation Island]] in the [[South Atlantic Ocean]]. It was named after the [[Endurance Expedition]] of 1914–1917, and its name was approved by the [[Advisory Committee for Undersea Features]] in June 1987.<ref name="ca-Shackleton_Endurance"/><ref name="gnis"/>

