{{short description|A list of the relatively moving sections of the lithosphere of the Earth}}
[[Image:Plates tect2 en.svg|thumb|The 15 major plates]]
[[Image:Plate tectonics map.gif|thumb|Plate tectonics map from NASA]]

This is a '''list of tectonic plates''' on the Earth's surface. [[Plate tectonics|Tectonic plates]] are pieces of [[Earth's crust]] and uppermost [[Mantle (geology)|mantle]], together referred to as the [[lithosphere]]. The plates are around {{convert|100|km|mi|abbr=on}} thick and consist of two principal types of material: [[oceanic crust]] (also called ''[[Sima (geology)|sima]]'' from [[silicon]] and [[magnesium]]) and [[continental crust]] (''[[sial]]'' from silicon and [[aluminium]]). The composition of the two types of crust differs markedly, with  [[mafic]] [[basalt]]ic rocks dominating oceanic crust, while continental crust consists principally of lower-[[density]] [[felsic]] [[granite|granitic]] rocks.

