The following is a timeline of the [[Ljubljana#History|history]] of the city of [[Ljubljana]], [[Slovenia]]. {{Dynamic list}} {{TOC right}}
==Prior to 19th century== {{see also|Emona}} {{History of Slovenia}}
* 1270 – [[Ottokar II of Bohemia]] in power.<ref name=MunicipalityHistory /> * 1277 – Habsburgs in power.{{sfn|Britannica|1910}} * 1335 – Town becomes capital of [[Carniola]], province of the Holy Roman Empire.<ref name=MunicipalityHistory>{{cite web |url=http://www.ljubljana.si/en/about-ljubljana/history/ |title=History of Ljubljana |publisher=Municipality of Ljubljana |accessdate=30 November 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150908133217/http://www.ljubljana.si/en/about-ljubljana/history/ |archivedate=8 September 2015 |df=dmy-all }} (includes timeline)</ref> * 1370 – [[St. Bartholomew's Church (Ljubljana)|St. Bartholomew's Church]] first mentioned. * 1461 – [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Ljubljana|Roman Catholic diocese of Laibach]] established.<ref name=katolsk>{{cite web |title=Chronology of Catholic Dioceses: Slovenia |url=http://www.katolsk.no/organisasjon/verden/chronology/slovenia |publisher=[[Roman Catholic Diocese of Oslo]] |location=Norway |accessdate=30 November 2015 }}</ref> * 1484 – [[Ljubljana Town Hall|Town Hall]] built. * 1504 – [[Janez Lantheri]] becomes first elected mayor.<ref name=MunicipalityHistory /> * 1511 – [[1511 Idrija earthquake]].<ref name=MunicipalityHistory /> * 1536 – Protestant Latin school established.<ref name=MunicipalityHistory /> * 1599 – Jesuit school established.<ref name=MunicipalityHistory /> * 1622 – 5 May: [[1622 Slovenia earthquake]]. * 1658 – {{Interlanguage link multi|Auersperg Palace, Ljubljana|sl|3=Turjaška palača}} built. * 1660 – [[Franciscan Church of the Annunciation]] built. * 1693 – [[Academia Operosorum Labacensium]] founded.<ref name="Plut2007">{{cite book|author1= Leopoldina Plut-Pregelj |author2= Carole Rogel |title= A to Z of Slovenia|year=2007 |edition=2nd |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield|isbn=978-0-8108-7216-5 |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=Kt7NUorHcKAC&pg=PR21 }}</ref> * 1701 – Academia Philharmonicorum Labacensis founded.<ref name="Plut2007" /> * 1703 – [[Tivoli Castle]] built. * 1707 – [[Ljubljana Cathedral|St. Nicholas's Cathedral]] rebuilt. * 1747 – [[Visitation of Mary Church (Ljubljana)|Visitation of Mary Church]] built. * 1751 – [[Robba Fountain]] installed in the [[Town Square (Ljubljana)|Town Square]]. * 1755 – [[Cekin Mansion]] built. * 1767 – Society of Agriculture and the Useful Arts in the Duchy of Carniola founded.<ref name=parrott>{{cite web |url= http://www.scholarly-societies.org/chronology_soc.html |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304115228/http://www.scholarly-societies.org/chronology_soc.html |deadurl=yes |archivedate=4 March 2016 |title=Chronology of Scholarly Societies |editor=Jim Parrott |work=Scholarly Societies Project |publisher=[[University of Waterloo]] |location=Canada }}</ref> * 1777 – [[Gruber Palace]] built. * 1778 – ''[[Laibacher Zeitung]]'' German-language newspaper begins publication. * 1780 – {{Interlanguage link multi|Gruber Canal|sl|3=Gruberjev kanal}} constructed (approximate date).<ref name=MunicipalityHistory /> * 1797 – Town occupied by French forces.
==19th century== * 1809 – Town occupied by French forces again.<ref name=MunicipalityHistory /> * 1810 – [[Ljubljana Botanical Garden|Botanical Garden]] established.<ref name=botanic>{{cite web |url= http://www.bgci.org/garden_search.php?action=Find&ftrCountry=SI |title=Garden Search: Slovenia |publisher= [[Botanic Gardens Conservation International]] |location=London |accessdate=30 November 2015 }}</ref> * 1813 – French occupation ends.<ref name=MunicipalityHistory /> * 1821 ** January–May: International [[Congress of Laibach|congress]] held in Laibach.<ref name=MunicipalityHistory /> ** [[Congress Square]] laid out. ** [[National Museum of Slovenia|Estate Museum of Carniola]] founded. * 1837 – [[Casino Building]] constructed. * 1842 – [[Triple Bridge|Franz's Bridge]] built.{{sfn|Costa|1848}} * 1848 – [[Ljubljana railway station|Railway station]] built. * 1849 – Vienna-Laibach railroad begins operating.<ref name="Plut2007" /> * 1857 – [[Trieste]]-Laibach railway built.<ref name=MunicipalityHistory /> * 1861 – Gas lighting installed.<ref name=MunicipalityHistory /> * 1867 – [[Hradecky Bridge]] built. * 1869 – Population: 22,593.<ref name=MunicipalityHistory /> * 1871 – Tobačna Ljubljana (tobacco factory) begins operating.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mgml.si/en/city-museum-of-ljubljana-377/tobacco-museum-960/ |title=Tobacco Museum |work=City Museum of Ljubljana |publisher=Municipality of Ljubljana |accessdate=30 November 2015 }}</ref> * 1889 – Vodnik statue erected in [[Vodnik Square]]. * 1890 ** Waterworks introduced.<ref name=MunicipalityHistory /> ** Population: 30,691.<ref>{{cite book |title=[[Statesman's Year-Book]] |year=1899 |location=London |publisher= Macmillan and Co.|chapter= Austria-Hungary: Austria |chapterurl=http://hdl.handle.net/2027/nyp.33433081590550?urlappend=%3Bseq=729 }}</ref> * 1892 – [[Slovenian National Opera and Ballet Theatre|Provincial Theatre]] built. * 1895 – 14 April: [[1895 Ljubljana earthquake|Earthquake]].{{sfn|Britannica|1910}} * 1897 – [[Ljubljana Central Pharmacy|Central Pharmacy]] built. * 1898 – [[Kresija Palace]] built. * 1899 – [[Government and Presidential Palace (Ljubljana)|Government Palace]] built.
==20th century==
* 1901 ** [[Trams in Ljubljana|Tram]] begins operating.<ref name=MunicipalityHistory /> ** [[Dragon Bridge (Ljubljana)|Dragon Bridge]] built. * 1903 – [[Jek Bridge]] rebuilt. * 1905 ** [[Grand Hotel Union]] built. ** [[Prešeren Monument (Ljubljana)|Prešeren Monument]] erected on [[Prešeren Square]]. * 1907 – [[Mladika (building complex)|Mladika]] built. * 1908 – [[Slovene Philharmonic Orchestra]] active. * 1911 – [[Ljubljana National Drama Theatre|Theatre]] built on {{Interlanguage link multi|Erjavec Street|sl|3=Erjavčeva cesta, Ljubljana}}.[http://www.en.drama.si/about-drama/o_zgodovini_stavbe_sng_drama_ljubljana] * 1918 ** City becomes part of the newly established [[Kingdom of Serbs, Croats and Slovenians]].<ref name=MunicipalityHistory /> ** [[National Gallery of Slovenia]] founded.<ref name=MunicipalityHistory /> ** [[St. Peter's Bridge]] rebuilt. * 1919 ** [[University of Ljubljana]]<ref name="Plut2007" /> and {{Interlanguage link multi|Ljubljana Music Conservatory|sl|3=Ljubljanski glasbeni konservatorij}} founded. ** [[Ljubljana National Drama Theatre]] in use. ** Population: 60,000.<ref>{{cite book |title=Statesman's Year-Book |year=1921 |location=London |publisher= Macmillan and Co.|chapter= Serb, Croat and Slovene State |chapterurl= http://hdl.handle.net/2027/njp.32101072368440?urlappend=%3Bseq=1320 }}</ref> * 1923 – Palace Theatre built.<ref name=cinema>{{cite web |url= http://cinematreasures.org/theaters/slovenia/ljubljana?status=all |title=Movie Theaters in Ljubljana, Slovenia |work=CinemaTreasures.org |publisher= Cinema Treasures LLC |location=Los Angeles |accessdate=30 November 2015 }}</ref> * 1933 – [[Nebotičnik]] hi-rise built.<ref name=heilbrunn11eusb>{{cite web |url=http://www.metmuseum.org/toah/ht/?period=11&region=eusb#/Key-Events |title= Balkan Peninsula, 1900 A.D.–present: Key Events |work= Heilbrunn Timeline of Art History |publisher=[[Metropolitan Museum of Art]] |location=New York |accessdate=30 November 2015 }}</ref> * 1935 – [[City Museum of Ljubljana]] established. * 1937 – {{Interlanguage link multi|Hotel Slon|sl}} on [[Čop Street]] rebuilt. * 1938 – [[Slovenian Academy of Sciences and Arts|Academy of Sciences and Arts]] founded.<ref name="Plut2007" /> * 1939 ** [[Ljubljana Central Market]] built. ** [[Academy of Music (Ljubljana)|Academy of Music]] active. * 1941 ** April: City annexed by Italy.<ref name=EuropaChronology2003>{{cite book |publisher=Europa Publications |title= Political Chronology of Europe |year= 2003|isbn=978-1-135-35687-3 |chapter= Slovenia |chapterurl= https://books.google.com/books?id=hVNvCz0c_gsC&pg=PA234 |pages=234+ }}</ref> ** [[National and University Library of Slovenia]] building constructed.<ref name=heilbrunn11eusb /> * 1942 – "Occupiers surrounded Ljubljana with a 30-kilometre barb wire fence."<ref name=MunicipalityHistory /> * 1943 – German occupation begins.<ref name=MunicipalityHistory /> * 1945 ** Occupation ends.<ref name=MunicipalityHistory /> ** [[Academy of Theatre, Radio, Film and Television (Ljubljana)|Academy of Theatre]] established. ** [[Ljubljanica Sluice Gate]] built. * 1951 ** {{Interlanguage link multi|Ljubljana trolleybus|sl|3=Ljubljanski trolejbus}} begins operating. ** ''[[Dnevnik (Slovenia)|Dnevnik]]'' newspaper begins publication.<ref name="europa2004">{{cite book|author=[[Europa Publications ]]|title=Central and South-Eastern Europe 2004 |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=5J_gAU8c9NIC&pg=PA642 |year=2003|publisher=[[Europa Publications]] |isbn=978-1-85743-186-5 |chapter=Slovenia }}</ref> * 1953 – Population: 138,211.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://unstats.un.org/unsd/demographic/products/dyb/1950_round.htm |work=Demographic Yearbook 1955 |year= |publisher=[[Statistical Office of the United Nations]] |location=New York |title=Population of capital city and cities of 100,000 or more inhabitants }}</ref> * 1955 – [[Biennial of Graphic Arts (Ljubljana)]] begins. * 1959 – [[Exhibition and Convention Centre (Ljubljana)]] built. * 1965 ** [[Tivoli Hall]] (arena) opens in [[Tivoli City Park]]. ** SKB bank established.<sup>([[:sl:SKB|sl]])</sup> * 1966 – {{Interlanguage link multi|OHO (art group)|sl|3=Skupina OHO}} formed.<ref name=heilbrunn11eusb /> * 1971 ** [[City bus service no. 1 (Ljubljana)]] begins operating. ** Population: 173,853 city; 213,298 urban agglomeration.<ref>{{cite book |url= https://unstats.un.org/unsd/demographic/products/dyb/1970_round.htm |title=Demographic Yearbook 1975 |year=1976 |author=[[United Nations Department of Economic and Social Affairs]], Statistical Office |location=New York |chapter=Population of capital city and cities of 100,000 and more inhabitants |pages=253-279 }}</ref> * 1982 – [[Cankar Hall]] built. * 1984 – [[Druga godba]] music festival begins. * 1985 – [[Trail of Remembrance and Comradeship]] created. * 1990 – [[Ljubljana International Film Festival]] begins. * 1991 ** 25 June: Ljubljana designated capital of newly declared independent Slovenia.<ref name=MunicipalityHistory /> ** 27 June: Airport bombed by [[Yugoslav People's Army]].<ref name=EuropaChronology2003 /> ** ''[[Slovenske novice]]'' newspaper begins publication.<ref name="Biggins2000">{{cite book|editor1=Michael Biggins |editor2=Janet Crayne |title=Publishing in Yugoslavia's Successor States|url= https://books.google.com/books?id=0g1CIRHeO4YC&pg=PA24 |year=2000|publisher= [[Haworth Press]] |location=New York |isbn=978-0-7890-1046-9}}</ref> * 1993 – [[Prule Bridge]] built. * 1999 – [[General Maister Monument (Brdar)]] erected.
==21st century==
* 2001 ** [[Noisefest]] begins. ** Kolosej Ljubljana cinema opens.<ref name=cinema /> * 2004 – May: Slovenia becomes part of the European Union.<ref name=MunicipalityHistory /> * 2005 ** 31 October: SKB bank robbery occurs.<sup>([[:sl:2005|sl]])</sup> ** November: Economic protest.<ref name=bbc-timeline>{{cite web |url= https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-17847681 |work=BBC News |title= Slovenia Profile: Timeline |accessdate=30 November 2015 }}</ref> * 2006 ** [[Filofest]] of student films begins. ** [[Zoran Janković (politician)|Zoran Janković]] becomes mayor. * 2010 - City named [[World Book Capital]] by UNESCO. * 2011 – "[[Tito street decision in Slovenia|Tito Street]]" issue decided. * 2012 – November: Anti-austerity [[2012–13 Slovenian protests]] begin.<ref name=bbc-timeline /> * 2014 – Population: 277,554.
