{{History of Nigeria}} This is a '''timeline of the [[history]] of [[Port Harcourt]]''', the capital of [[Rivers State]], Nigeria. {{Dynamic list}}
==19th century== {{Expand section|date=July 2014}}
==20th century== {{Expand section|date=July 2014}} [[Image:Port_Harcourt_in_1930s.JPG|thumb|right|Port Harcourt in 1930s]] * 1925 - [[Braithwaite Memorial Hospital]] begins operating. * 1961 - [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Port Harcourt]] established. * 1965 - [[Port Harcourt Refining Company]] founded. * 1971 - Newspaper ''[[The Tide (Nigeria)|The Tide]]'' begins publication.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.thetidenewsonline.com/about/|title=About Us|publisher=''The Tide News''|date= |accessdate=2014-05-03}}</ref> * 1972 ** Rivers State College of Science and Technology opens. ** [[Sharks F.C.|Sharks football club]] formed. * 1975 ** University College, Port Harcourt created<ref>http://cdnetng.org/?q=node/72</ref> ** [[Port Harcourt Zoo]] established. * 1977 - University College gains University status becomes [[University of Port Harcourt]]. * 1980 ** [[Rivers State University of Science and Technology]] replaces Rivers State College of Science and Technology. ** [[University of Port Harcourt Teaching Hospital]] in operation. * 1981 - [[Radio Rivers 99.1|Radio Rivers]] begins broadcasting.<ref name="radio rivers">{{cite news|url=http://www.thetidenewsonline.com/2014/05/07/radio-rivers-at-33/|title=Radio Rivers At 33 |date=2014-05-07|work=[[The Tide (Nigeria)|The Tide]]|language=|location=[[Port Harcourt]], [[Nigeria]]|publisher=Rivers State Newspaper Corporation|accessdate=2014-06-29}}</ref> * 1984 - Rivers State School of Basic Studies commences in Port Harcourt. * 1985 - [[Rivers State Television]] inaugurated. * 1988 - [[Dolphins F.C. (Port Harcourt)|Dolphins football club]] is founded. * 1993 - Sister-city relationship with [[Kansas City, Missouri|Kansas City]] formed.<ref name="kcsister"/> * 1995 - [[Ken Saro-Wiwa]] and [[Ogoni Nine]] buried in [[Port Harcourt Cemetery]].<ref name="cemetery1">{{cite web|url=http://www.deseretnews.com/article/450161/NIGERIAS-MILITARY-LEADERS-HANG-PLAYWRIGHT-AND-8-OTHER-ACTIVISTS.html?pg=all|title=Nigeria's Military Leaders Hang Playwright And 8 Other Activists|work=[[Deseret News|Deseretnews.com]]|publisher=[[Deseret News Publishing Company]]|date=1995-11-11 |accessdate=2014-07-07}}</ref> * 1996 - [[Meridian Hospital]] begins operating. * 1999 - Rivers State School of Basic Studies revamped and renamed to [[Rivers State College of Arts and Science]].
==21st century== {{Expand section|date=July 2014}} * 2001 - [[Liberation Stadium]] opens.<ref name="lbs ph">{{cite web|url=http://www.worldstadiums.com/stadium_pictures/africa/nigeria/port_harcourt_liberation.shtml |title=Liberation Stadium (Port Harcourt)|publisher=World Stadiums|date= |accessdate=6 August 2014}}</ref>
* 2004 ** Population: 1,133,400.<ref name="kcsister">{{cite web|url=http://www.kcsistercities.org/sister-cities/port-harcourt-nigeria|title=Port Harcourt, Nigeria|publisher=Kcsistercities.org|date= |accessdate=14 August 2014}}</ref> ** ''[[National Network (newspaper)|National Network]]'' newspaper begins publication.<ref name="anniversary">{{cite web| url=http://www.modernghana.com/news/364688/1/seventh-year-anniversary-celebration-national-netw.html|title=Seventh Year Anniversary Celebration National Network Makes History|publisher=ModernGhana.com|last=Kwaaba|first=Frank|date=2 December 2011|accessdate=19 June 2014}}</ref> * 2005 - [[Sosoliso Airlines Flight 1145]] crashes. * 2006 ** [[Port Harcourt International Airport]] stop operations for maintenance. ** Population: 1,382,592. * 2008 ** Garden City Literary Festival begins.<ref>[http://www.portharcourtbookfestival.com/index.php/about-phbf About]</ref> ** [[Street Rhymes Studios]] in business.<ref name="neighbourhod newspaper"/> * 2009 - [[Port Harcourt International Airport]] named Nigeria's third busiest airport. * 2010 - [[Nigerian bus electrocutions|Bus electrocution]]s accident. * 2011 - [[91.7 FM (Port Harcourt)|91.7 FM]] begins broadcasting.<ref name="radio ph002">{{cite web|url=http://digicastmagazine.com/issue/september-2011/article/all-new-radio-port-harcourt-commissioned|title=All New Radio Port Harcourt, Commissioned|publisher=Digicast Magazine|date=2 September 2011 |accessdate=12 July 2014}}</ref> * 2012 ** Port Harcourt selected 2014 [[World Book Capital]].<ref>https://www.un.org/apps/news/story.asp?NewsID=42448</ref> ** Massacre of four Uniport students.<ref>https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-19869492</ref> * 2013 ** [[Kelsey Harrison Hospital|Kelsey Harrison]] and [[Rivers State Dental and Maxillofacial Hospital|Rivers State Dental and Maxillofacial]] hospitals start to function.<ref name="tide newspaper1">{{cite news|url=http://www.thetidenewsonline.com/2013/02/04/%E2%80%98ph-new-hub-for-medical-tourism%E2%80%99/|title=PH, New Hub For Medical Tourism|last=|first=|date=4 February 2013|work=[[The Tide (Nigeria)|The Tide]]|language=|location=[[Port Harcourt]]|publisher=Rivers State Newspaper Corporation|accessdate=15 July 2014}}</ref> ** ''I'm on Fire'' becomes most successful mixtape by a Port Harcourt-based artist.<ref name="neighbourhod newspaper">{{cite news|url=http://www.theneighbourhoodonline.com/fashionnew/2829-street-rhymes-studios-heats-up-port-harcourt-music-scene.html|title=Street Rhymes Studios heats up Port Harcourt music scene |date=2014-05-26|work=The Neighbourhood Newspaper|language=|location=[[Port Harcourt]], [[Nigeria]]|publisher=Nativity Communications Company|accessdate=2014-07-01}}</ref> ** [[Port Harcourt International Fashion Week]] begins. ** Garden City Literary Festival gets new name: [[Port Harcourt Book Festival]].<ref>http://allafrica.com/stories/201308051431.html</ref> * 2014 - Port Harcourt [[World Book Capital]] takes place.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.punchng.com/columnists/pocket-lawyer/port-harcourt-unesco-world-book-capital-2014/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-07-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140630021552/http://www.punchng.com/columnists/pocket-lawyer/port-harcourt-unesco-world-book-capital-2014/ |archivedate=2014-06-30 |df= }}</ref>
