{{Infobox lake | name = Övre Rudasjön | image = Ovre Rudasjon.jpg | caption = as seen from the commuter railway station | image_bathymetry = | caption_bathymetry = | location = [[Haninge Municipality]], south [[Stockholm County]] | coords = {{coord|59|10|8.94|N|18|08|2.30|E|region:SE_type:waterbody_scale:100000|display=inline,title}} | type = | inflow = [[Trylen]], [[Nedre Rudasjön]] | outflow = [[Dammträsk]], [[Drevviken]] | catchment = | basin_countries = Sweden | length = | width = | area = {{convert|0.113|km2|abbr=on}} | depth = {{convert|3.4|m|abbr=on}}<ref name="SMHI"/> | max-depth = {{convert|8.1|m|abbr=on}}<ref name="SMHI" /> | volume = {{convert|0.386|km3|acre.ft|abbr=on}}<ref name="SMHI" /> | residence_time = | shore = | elevation = {{convert|34.5|m|abbr=on}}<ref name="SöEko"/> | islands = 0 | cities = [[Haninge Municipality|Haninge]], [[Handen]] | reference = <ref name="SMHI">SMHI, p 131</ref><ref name="SöEko">Södertörnsekologerna, p 8</ref><ref name="VISS">Vattenmyndigheterna</ref> }} '''Övre Rudasjön''' ([[Swedish language|Swedish]] for "Upper [[Crucian carp]] Lake"), or '''Övre Rudan''' for short, is a [[lake]] in [[Haninge Municipality]], 18&nbsp;km (11&nbsp;mi) south of central [[Stockholm]], [[Sweden]]. Forming part of the [[Tyresån Lake System]], its major inflow comes from lakes [[Nedre Rudasjön]] ("Lower Crucian carp Lake") and [[Trylen]] to the south, while its outflow passes over [[Dammträsk]] into [[Drevviken]] to the north.
The tall buildings of [[Handen]] commercial centre along the eastern shore of the lake contrast the dense forest of the [[Rudan Open-air Area]] on the opposite shore. The proximity to the [[Stockholm commuter rail|commuter rail]] station at Handen, makes the lake easily accessible to a large number of people, while the forests surrounding it makes it attractive to open-air lovers. It is used for bathing in summers and [[cross-country skiing]] in winters.<ref>''Övre Rudan'', Tyresåsamarbetet</ref>
Compared to other lakes in the Tyresån Lake System, levels of phosphorus in the lake are moderate.<ref>''Appendix 5'' (PDF), Tyresåsamarbetet</ref>
{| class="wikitable" |+ Nutrition levels<ref>''Aktuellt näringstillstånd'', Stockholm County Council</ref> ! [[Phosphorus|PTOT]] !! [[Nitrogen|NTOT]] !! N/P-quota !! [[Chlorophyll|Chlor]] !! Sight depth !! Colour !! [[Total organic carbon|TOC]] !! [[pH]] !! [[Alkalinity|Alk]] |- | 17&nbsp;ug/l || 456&nbsp;ug/l || 27 || 6 a ug/l || 3,8 m (max) || 34&nbsp;mg/l || 8&nbsp;mg/l || 7,2 || 0,28 mekv/l |}
With are 28 species of [[vascular plant]]s by the lake and 1 species of [[Charales|Stoneworth]] in it, the lake fauna is considered relatively rich in species.<ref name="SöEko" />
